# Strict Approval Protocol

1. NEVER dispatch a new sub-agent for a subsequent phase without EXPLICIT user approval.
2. ALWAYS present the research, findings, or specification documents to the user for review FIRST.
3. ONLY after the user says "looks good", "go ahead", or otherwise confirms, may you proceed to TDD/Implementation.
4. DO NOT speed run. We are taking our time to get the architecture right.
5. If the user asks a series of questions, answer ALL of them clearly before asking for permission to proceed.